-- Serbia’s Energoprojekt Wins Construction Contract in Russia
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-05-04T10:27:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/serbia-s-energoprojekt-wins-construction-contract-in-russia.html
Energoprojekt Holding AD (ENHL) , a Serbian
construction and energy company, signed a 7.9 million-euro ($10
million) contract to build homes in Syktyvkar, the capital of
Russia’s northern Komi Republic.  Energoprojekt ’s  Visokogradnja (EPVI)  unit signed the agreement
with the Fund for Residential Construction of the city of
Syktyvkar d.o.o. and will complete the project by September
2013, the Belgrade-based company said in an e-mailed statement.  The value of Energoprojekt’s new contracts in the first
quarter almost tripled from a year ago, to 44 million euros, and
the latest agreement brings the total to almost 52 million
euros. Continuing projects are worth more than 300 million
euros, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  The company’s  shares  traded at 440 dinars at noon in
 Belgrade  today, 1.62 percent above yesterday’s close and 10.46
percent higher than at the end of last year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
